cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method for depth completion using a convolutional neural network. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions the application of the proposed method in real-world autonomous driving, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes an end-to-end method that learns to predict an error-map of depth regression task using a neural network. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a method for improving the accuracy of depth estimation, which is a common task in AI. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition - Conference) is a possible category as the paper presents results on the Kitti depth completion dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research and evaluated at the CVPR conference.
